- modules are python files
- packages are folders
- packages will have a __init__.py file by default
- when you import something in python:
  - finds the module
  - runs the code - adds the code to memory (pycache)
  - next line
- __name__ is used to get the name of a module, e.g. print(__name__)
- __main__ is the name given to the file running (files using it as an import will not be __main__)
- to check the module name: --> if __name__ == '__main__'
- python module index: https://docs.python.org/3/py-modindex.html
- help() offers documentation for modules e.g. help(random)
- dir() shows all available methods of a module e.g. dir(random)

Package installation
- python package index: https://pypi.org/
- pip3 install [package_name]==[version]

Virtual environments
- separate package environment created for each project
- options when creating a new project
  - venv: built-in in PyCharm
  - pipenv: created by python

